<a href="#0" id="0">We formulated the task of recognizing implied predicate-argument relationships within textual inference scenarios.</a>
<a href="#1" id="1">We compared this task to the labeling task of SemEval 2010, where no prior information about candidate arguments in the text is available.</a>
<a href="#2" id="2">We point out that in textual inference scenarios the candidate predicate and argument are given by the Hypothesis, while the challenge is only to verify that a predicate-argument relationship between these candidates is implied from the given Text.</a>
